caption: At this place I very much like their sushi, they deliver or you can take out. Friendly staff and made well.  Many good items to consider.  Street parking. No needed and cash or credit is accepted.

Absolutely incredible.. I've lived down the block since November an never been able to stop in until this evening. In my first 32yrs I tried my first boba tea. I got the strawberry with green tea an tapioca boba. It was so goood I'm wondering why haven't I tried it sooner. The chick was very friendly it was nice an cozy inside. I'm glad I got to try this place🖤
Great food, great neighbors. great staff

Great service from our sever Noah (I believe was his name). He was swamped with running all the outdoor dining tables while also taking care of takeout orders amongst other things he still had to attend to all by himself. He did a great job and made our 1 year anniversary a great experience. He even went the extra mile helping me surprise my girlfriend with some flowers and things I snuck in to him last minute and brought it out to surprise her at the end of dinner. Thanks Noah and Runa for the great night out and experience it won't be forgotten! Make this a date night destination on your list!

I had the ribeye steak teriyaki. At $27.00 I avoided it for a while but this dish is totally worth it.  This is the first time I tried something non-fish related and considering that it’s takeout they did a really good job making sure it wasn’t overcooked (medium rare) which was great because I was planning on having it for lunch the next day.  Their take-out is just as good as if you were to eat it there. I like this place because it has good quality fish and they’re consistent.
Excellent sushi!

Came here on a date before a rehearsal and the Runa Bucktown Asian Gourmet was delightful. Portions were good and the manager helped us out that day and was absolutely terrific. I had the salmon bowl and my boyfriend had tuna. The toppings were all good and this place just has standard, good Runa Bucktown Asian Gourmet.

Honestly the best sushi we’ve found in Chicago. Ingredients taste super fresh and the price is an amazing value. We love the lobster maki and ocean maki (get the Flaming Runa if you love spicy) and the crab ravioli appetizer was phenomenal. Patio is tented with heat lamps and BYOB!
Great sushi and great service—Prices were normal for the city and we loved the patio area! Also, BYOB!
Super Delicious and Awesome Service!
Rocky was our server. He was super nice and informative! I would definitely recommend 😁 The rolls are yummy!
Love this place! Our go-to for sushi in the neighborhood. Cute little outdoor patio.

We arrived at this place for lunch. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was very successful. The staff members were very polite and we had a fantastic feeling. The meal was delicious. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. we highly recommend this place.
Good location for japanese food. Got there about two, it was not packed.
This place blows
Great sushi 0!!
Best sushi ever. Highly recommend. Amazing service. Get the flaming runa! And Toro!

Everything I've had here is great quality! I am especially in love with the pork tonkatsu!! Indoor dining was not yet open, but they have a great patio space that was open for business when we went on 06-06-2020! The food here makes for quality take-out, but nothing beats dining on the patio in my opinion!
Honestly the best Asian food I've ever had. Really really good me quality and everything as though his fantastic. One time they must up the order and gave me a the entire meal for free. Good people

It was my family’s first time trying them out and my daughters first time try Pho and I tell you all this is going to be my new date night spot after all this virus stuff goes away. So for now date night’s at home will consist of Runa food. Very pleased
Consistently good sushi with exceptional presentation
Great food . Besides Miami, I will not eat sushi anywhere else
Some of the best sushi in the entire country, certainly the Midwest. Don't miss the veggie hot & sour soup! A++
I enjoyed my sake nirgri as well as the warm customer service and cool open vibe I'll definitely be back. Great price for great service.
Love this place.  Ask for the holy Henry so fresh so amazing.
Love this place .alot of different sushi are new to me . And the freshness and taste are awesome

This is our go-to neighborhood sushi spot. Always tasty, very consistent, great staff when dinning in, and quick when ordering carryout. The fish always has good color, texture, and flavor. The rolls are well constructed too. Their Spicy Scallop roll is a personal favorite, and the way they do their shitake mushroom roll, with fried shallots is unique and tasty. Runa is never disappointing. We've been many times, and will be back many more.

Pretty cute spot. The sushi is a bit above average but the garlic edamame is some of the best I've ever had.  Love the outdoor patio and you always score points for BYOB.  Nothing super unique about their rolls but cool neighborhood place to eat outside.
Fats and friendly service

(Translated by Google) When I asked for miso soup, I was asked "Is it spicy but are you okay?" I tried to enjoy Japanese taste at a Japanese restaurant but failed ...  (Original) ミソスープを頼んだら「スパイシーですが大丈夫ですか？（英語）」って聞かれて、何言ってんだろうと思って飲んでみたら本当に辛かった。ジャパニーズレストランで日本の味を楽しもうとしたけど失敗…。

This place has fantastic ambiance. There's a really cool mural on the back wall of the restaurant and the outdoor seating has romantic lighting that you can see at night and cherry blossom limbs that you can see during the day. Perfect place for a date or just some Japanese food. The food was pretty good (would eat here again) but not the best sushi I've ever had (that sushi was more expensive than I would like to mention) Average price for a sushi place (sushi is always kinda expensive). The only not great thing was that our waitress was kinda slow and would forget some of the things we asked for, but I'm sure that's not something that happens all the time.
Curry chicken

Hidden gem and sooo delicious! A fun twist on a sushi menu and overall creative and tasty food! Loved the spicy tuna “ravioli”!! Bonus that it’s BYOB and has a patio. Great service, will come again and again! :)
One of the restaurants My wife and I spent our 9th anniversary at. I loved it. So glad we came.
Henry is fantastic. 10/10. Love this spot.

Good sushi, a little pricey, byob. He first sentence says it all. The food is good, pretty creative sushi rolls, solid appetizer selection. It is a little pricey compared to some other sushi places, but it’s byob, so that nice, you can save a few bucks by bringing your own beer/wine.

I usually love this place but I just placed an order for steamed rice and received less than half a container "full". Two of those Lil bowls half filled. I'm annoyed, especially since it's raining and my husband doesn't think it's worth going back for. Should've just cooked my own rice at home. 🤦🏻‍♀️🤬
Great sushi! Good gyoza too!
Best sushi I have ever had!! From Colorado visiting Chicago for the first time and so happy that our local friends suggested Runa's. Henry is the man!!! Beast maki, flaming runa to die for!!!
Great Food, Possibly Best in the city.
This place has Great food that is super tasty, amazing flavors. Can't wait to go back and try other dishes!
A great Japanese restaurant. My favorite Asian spot in Wicker Park/Bucktown! Don't hesitate to order some appetizers for the table and bring your party a bottle of wine!

Have had take out and/or delivery from here at least 5 times now and have never been disappointed! food always taste fresh and delicious. The guys working there are always friendly, both in the restaurant and delivery. Great value for our money!

The food is really solid. Nothing made me re think my feelings on food or raw fish, but it was nonetheless good. The service, on the other hand, fantastic. Our server was very attentive and had suggestions on what to order. I would go again, but probably wouldn't make this place my go to sushi joint.
My neighborhood place for sushi.  Always top quality, but don't overlook the robata and szechuan fare, which more than hold their own.
Best place for sushi hands down

Great neighborhood sushi/Japanese food restaurant.  The owner is super nice and the staff is pretty great.  I tend towards the cooked foods so I thought the steak was excellent.  The sushi is fresh and tasty too.
Great staff, nice vibe, FANTASTIC SUSHI.
Have eaten here several times, love it.  My oldest kid has eaten sushi all over world and this is her favorite in Chicago.
This place is beyond amazing. Came in after midnight and the sushi was fantastic! Will definitely be back when I'm in town.
hands down our favorite late night spot! open til 2am most nights. fresh sushi, nice staff, 5 stars
For what you pay the sushi is great and the service is too. Don't put it on oar with more expensive places just judge it for what it is and you'll be satisfied. It's also byob.

Hands down friendliest staff ever and FRESHEST sushi. Everyone we've had was so kind and accomodating... with so many other sushi spots in the area to try, this place is still better than them all. It's got the reputation and consistent excellence every time :)
Best sushi in chicago
I love this place the food was great and nothing was wrong come here if you haven't.  Delaney on her 9th bday
Great service and quiet scene
delicious food, definitely recommend, awesome sushi

The most underrated Sushi restaurant in Chicago! Don't miss their Flaming Runa, a mouth watering roll that's grilled, I believe. Forget your boogie stance on cooked sushi. This one is a big winner! The sashimi is fresh, and the service is always fantastic.

Best Sushi hands down! Henry is always takes care of my wife and I whenever we come it. It is nice to go to a restaurant and the owner comes up to your table and engages in conversations with you and remembers who you are. Highly recommend!!!
Super great service, the food is unbelievable!!! Always so good!!!!

I'm a vegetarian and i discovered a few years ago that i love veggie maki rolls(have always hated eating fish too, so no fish more me...yuck!)  and at Runa I love love love their Hybrid GTR maki(the regular GTR roll has fish in it, so Im glad i have the substituute maki roll is right on the menu. In fact, of all the sushi places in Chicago Runa is my absolute favorite due to that one Hybrid GTR maki roll..in my opinion.it is perfection as far as the balancing of textures and flavors go. mmmmm.  In general whenever Runa chefs fry tempura veggies to put into a maki roll it is  ALWAYS cooked/fried just right. It seems like whenever I go to other sushi spots often the tempura sweet potato is undercooked a bit, especially if they dont cut the chunks thin enough or on the other end of the spectrum it is so cooked and hot it has the texture of instant mashed potatoes...but I have never been disappointed by Runa.  Once I did bring a friend from out of town with me to Runa who's a real connoisseur when it comes to sushi and he was overly joyful and impressed while eating there, just kept ordering more and more things, seemed like a kid Christmas morning, said the fish quality was amazing.  Vwry recently they added late night hours...open til 2am now! So if i have a late night sushi craving then i can easily scratch that itch...10/10
Fresh 🍣. Never disappoint me. Keep up da good work
Worth it!
Great food and wonderful staff. I used to live behind this restaurant and their miso soup saved me one winter when I got sick. I also enjoy their taste in music.
Great sushi! Has such a variety in the menu. I highly recommend this place. You can't go wrong with anything in the menu, the owner is so creative with anything new that he brings into the menu.
Racist
If you want a experience of a lot of different quality taste you will not go wrong with Runas! It is exceptional and consistent quality! Great atmosphere with excellent service!
Never will never return to this racist place

The owner is unprofessional, disrespectful and absolutely racist! He treats his black and brown customers poorly and he bring other people’s personal business to another attention in public.  Ruined a meeting that was being held at his restaurant and then demanded we leave.  We will boycott Runa for their racism.

Love Runa! We have gotten take out as well as dined in a few times now, and every time the food is fantastic. The garlic edamame and gyoza are delicious starters, and the sushi is some of the best in the city. Highly recommend Runa!
Good food. Good service
Love this place.  Great customer service and food is amazing
Extremely fresh fish... watching them fillet fish right in front of us!
Good sushi. Friendly staff. A bit higher priced compared to other local sushi places. Never had to wait for a table.
Great tunes as well
Love this
Great atmosphere, friendly staff,  reasonably priced.  Can't go wrong with Runa
We love Runa. BYOB (with a small fee). Like to go to go grocer and grab a bottle of sake for the meal. They have sake glasses along with wine and beer glasses with is cool.
Great food, good service. Byob ftw
Been here at least 10 times and spend around 100 bucks each time. Totally worth it, never disappointed
Absolutely amazing sushi. The quality is top notch. I would recommend this place to anyone looking for a great place to grab sushi! I will definitely be back.
Awesome lunch special
Delicious sushi! Good vibes here too.
Best sushi is Chicago. Henry the owner has a great set up with the best fresh fish in Chicago! Must try if you visit Chicago. I am a regular now and this place never disappoints! Love it.

I just ate here for the first time and it was incredible! I got the Vegan Monster Roll and all of the ingredients were unbelievably fresh. I was skeptical ordering sushi as takeout but they packaged everything perfectly. Will be eating here as often as I possibly can <3
Best Crab Ravioli I've ever tasted. I also highly recommend the Spicy Tuna Ravioli and Halloween Maki.
Sushi goodness at a reasonable price.

I'm curious to know how this place received 4.4 stars for a sushi place. I came here because of the "good reviews" and yet the sushi is average. The avocado was clearly not fresh and the fish was also not the freshest. I'm always trying new places for sushi and sadly this one didn't stand out like I thought It would.
Food takes a while, but tastes amazing

Best Japanese food in Wicker Park/Bucktown! The fish is high quality; no “fishy” taste. On top of that, super nice service, cozy space, and good music. BYOB aspect is great, too. Usually not super crowded, so you can actually hear your friends/date.
Frankly, I thought it was a little overpriced for what you get. I've had a much cheaper sushi that was just as good in the city. Still enjoyed the meal
Great Sushi!
Great Sushi

The food is okay, but service is really slow
Went in looking for Ramen came out with Mongolian beef. Very taste would recommend. Didn't have egg rolls that should have come with meal. Overall not bad!

Runa is one of the few places we keep coming back to. There are so many options for places to eat in Chicago that we just don't repeat visits to a lot of places but Runa is consistently good, reasonably priced, and always a nice environment to visit. Definitely worth your hard earned dollars and time!
First time visiting. The food was incredible and the portions were HUGE!  The wait staff was super friendly. It was a great experience. We will definitely be back!
Really good, creative sushi and awesome service, Dan is great! Also, not usually busy, affordable and BYOB. Love it.
Henry is the best in accommodating gluten free allergies. Best experience everyone! Happy sushi eater.😁😁

First time visit was delicious and we were able to get a seat right away outside. It's BYOB and the staff was super helpful in both making recommendations on food to eat and in chilling our brought in beverages.
Lived across the street for several years and it never failed to hit the spot when craving sushi. As fresh and as good as anywhere in the city.
Amazing and delicious! A must try!
Good service. Good food.
Good food

The food was expensive and the portions were quite tiny. I'm used to getting pretty full on specialty rolls, and my group had to order more food. It was tasty, but not quite worth it. The atmosphere was nice, but we felt a bit rushed throughout the second half of dinner. It's a BYOB place, so that was nice. Overall good, but not great.
Runa does a great job! Been coming since thy opened and always leave happy. The beast maki is a little musky but the other like 30 things I've eaten here were all delicious.
Very good food and very good service.
Went here a few days ago after about a year or so. I still love the place, but I wish they still had the ramen bowls I loved. The fried rice I got was good though.
Great service!  Joe recommended several sushi selection to our amazement it was delicious! .  First time,  but not our last.  Highly recommended thank you for your hospitality.
Good service
Wonderful, delicious and well priced.
Great sushi
Tastes like freshness
This a really nice space and the staff is super friendly. It's byob cozy spot and it's not too far from the rest of the action.
The Flaming Runa Roll was amazing, the place is nicely decorated, I not give it five stars for the slow service.
Fresh sushi, BYOB

If you're looking for a nice, chill sushi experience - this is the place. Great neighborhood spot, especially if you want to sit outside and enjoy the weather. Food was great, miso soup was on point, and the green tea was excellent.

Came here for dinner, but just thought the sushi was subpar.  The makis were very small and so were the sushi pieces.  We ordered the "Stay Rolling" specialty roll; it supposedly includes tuna, salmon, hamachi & avacado, but barely tasted any of the fishes!  We also ordered the Luv 1, which comes with 3 pieces of tuna, 3 pieces of salmon, 3 pieces of hamachi & spicy tuna maki.  Again, just subpar.
Solid sushi.
One of my favorite sushi spots in Chicago. Great food at a good price.
I am a sushi lover and i love their food here!!!!  Sashimi were thick slices, super fresh.   First time i had seafood miso---amazing!

Quaint little place in west Wicker Park. We started with edamame, lightly salted, and very fresh. I do not care for plain edamame, and this one did not disappoint. We also had the Negima Beef, teriyaki beef, rolled over an asparagus spear. This was also good, the asparagus was al dente, the way i like my veggies, and the beef was flavorful and tender. For our entrees, we both had some pieces of sushi and split a roll. The sushi was very fresh, the rice was not clumpy, but did not fall apart either upon dipping it in the soy sauce. We both enjoyed that very much. We shared a lobster maki roll. The lobster was tempura. While the roll was good, I would have preferred my lobster not be fried. The service was excellent, but we got there right after work, so there was not much of a crowd. Hard to really judge service when they only have a few people to wait on. Overall we enjoyed our dining experience and will dine there again.

Good food and nice lunch special portions but the male managing staff/waiter was unnecessarily rude with us even though we were the only customers in the restaurant at the time getting a take out lunch.
awesome place
Went on a Friday night for sushi.  Service was prompt and the portions were large.  I have recommended Runa to friends.

This is hands down the best restaurant in Wickerpark/Bucktown. I've been here a million times and have never experienced anything but consistent, quality service. They have the best salmon in the city, hands down. The sashimi is perfectly colored and prepared-  bursting with flavor and ridiculously fresh. The spicy seafood miso has no comparison, featuring a generous variety of seafood ranging from whitefish and crab to mussels and squid. It's a great date spot, great casual dinner, great outdoor patio, great delivery service, great dine-in service, and its BYOB. Can't say enough good things.  The owner, Henry, is a sushi master and is very hands-on with the customers and the food preparation. He flies fresh fish in from Hawaii daily, which is part of the unique freshness a meal there holds.
Awesome Place great food and service perfect for the grab and go late night.
Delicious, always fresh, and very kind staff. Back patio is a sweet spot too

Ah, who doesn't love good traditional Japanese cuisine? When I found out there was an actual restaurant that served those big steamy buns near me I had to try it out! Delivery is where my heart is when it's a cold day in Chicago so of course I'll let the delivery guy traverse this weather while I sit and watch my favorite tv shows from the comfort of my home (although I do hope they make it out alive).  After waiting...and waiting...and waiting....my order finally came after about an hour and 45 minutes when its probably about 2 miles from me at the most. Busy day? Yeah I get it, but at least give me a call if its going to be almost 2 hours. Finally, I got my hands on some steamy hot buns, chicken fried rice and some OJ! I bite into them..lo and behold! They're pretty bland and the BBQ Pork ones hardly had any meat. Something was off though, they were way too chewy almost like chewing a napkin. I kept thinking, did they cook them too long or nuke these things in the microwave? Then I take a minute to study the buns.... there was a thick piece of transparent paper on the bottom of them (transparent from all the moisture I assume) that I was accidentally ingesting as well. I wish they would've given a heads up about the invisible wax paper on the bottom of their buns before I started chowing down.  Removing the paper doesn't help though, proving that even though you can make the buns like nice with almost perfect texture, you can't make piss poor ingredients taste good. At this point I still have hope for the fried rice so "we'll see!!!" I say to myself, "I refuse to let the only Japanese restaurant near me be sub par!"  Fried rice tasted like straight vegetable oil, I still think it was poisoned.  You cannot taste the chicken or anything except for the crappy oil that it was drenched in. Along with the delayed delivery did I mention the container of fried rice was broken in the bag so I had to do some shenanigans just to get most of it out of the bag, some of it spilled on my floor and in the bag itself. Strike two Runa, but still I have hope for you. You're Japanese, you have standards of excellence!  Washing down meals with a good drink is the equivalent of breathing so I reach for my juice in the bag. I keep reaching and fiddling around. Did they forget my drink?  NOPE, they ripped me off and give me a something which I can only assume was meant for an infant that I paid 3 bucks for. For those who need visuals I'll describe it as best as I can. Think of a small pill bottle for like aspirin, yep, that's the size of the $3 drink they sold me (which didn't state that it was going to be in a can by the way). At this point I feel totally ripped off especially when I could've gone to 7-Eleven and got like a liter of OJ for 3-4 bucks. I drank my shot in less than a second and immediately grabbed my camera to take pictures.  I wouldn't recommend this place to anyone. If you want good Japanese buns go to Wow Bao. The pork ones at Runa are huge, but as I said before they hardly have any meat whatsoever and are pretty bland.

We've been here a handful of times and think this sushi is great, up there with the best in Chicago.  A few of our favorite rolls are the Pink Dragon Roll, Tuna Fantasy, the Black Pearl, and the Lobster Maki.  The beef udon is a great non-sushi option.  It's BYO, good for small or large groups of people, has a spacious patio out back for nice days, and last but not least, is a great option for delivery.

Don't let the small footprint fool you - while relatively new 2013, this is some of the best sushi in the city and rivals the best sushi in town.  Their specialty rolls are one of a kind, and all their sushi has been uber-fresh.  We've ordered again and again, each time excellent!  A real find and great addition to the Bucktown/Wicker Park area!
